# Backend Architecture

## Layered Structure (strict, no skip-layers)

```
Request → Router → Controller → Service → (Repository / external SDK)
```

| Layer | Responsibility | Must NOT |
|---|---|---|
| **Router** | Mount routes, attach middleware | Contain logic |
| **Controller** | Parse req, call service, format response via `ApiResponse` | Contain business logic |
| **Service** | All business logic, orchestration | Know about `req`/`res` |
| **Repository** | Data access only (DB, file, cache) | Contain business logic |

## Module Structure

Each feature lives in `src/modules/<feature>/`:
```
documents/
  documents.router.ts      ← express Router
  documents.controller.ts  ← request handling only
  documents.service.ts     ← business logic
  documents.schema.ts      ← Zod validation schemas
  documents.repository.ts  ← data access (add when DB lands)
```

## API Response — always use `ApiResponse` builder

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
res.status(200).json(ApiResponse.success(data));
res.status(201).json(ApiResponse.success(data, { message: 'Created' }));
res.status(400).json(ApiResponse.error('Validation failed', { errors }));

// ❌ BAD — raw shape, no envelope
res.json({ data });
res.json({ error: 'bad' });
```

## Validation — Zod at the controller boundary

```typescript
// documents.schema.ts
export const uploadQuerySchema = z.object({
  category: z.enum(['bill', 'prescription', 'insurance', 'other']).optional(),
});

// documents.controller.ts
import { validate } from '../../middleware/validate';
router.post('/upload', upload.single('file'), validate('body', uploadBodySchema), controller.upload);
```

## Error Handling

```typescript
// ✅ throw typed errors in services
import { AppError, NotFoundError, ValidationError } from '../../lib/AppError';

if (!doc) throw new NotFoundError('Document not found');

// The global errorHandler converts AppError → correct HTTP status automatically.
// Never catch-and-swallow in services — let errors bubble.
```

## Environment Config
- All env vars read through `src/config/env.ts` (Zod-validated at startup)
- Never `process.env.X` inline — always import from `config/env`

## Logging
- Use `logger` from `src/lib/logger.ts` — never `console.log` in production code
- Log level convention: `logger.info` for lifecycle, `logger.warn` for recoverable, `logger.error` for failures with stack

## File Organisation Rules
- No logic in `app.ts` or `index.ts` — wiring only
- Barrel exports (`index.ts`) at module root for clean imports
- Keep files under 200 lines; extract to sub-files otherwise
